trend_summary: Imagery shows a stable, tree-dominated suburb of detached houses. 2000-20XX: gradual residential infill, expansion of a northwest commercial node, new school/sports facilities added in the southwest, and minor arterial upgrades. Tree canopy stays extensive, even increasing as street trees mature. Overall pattern and density remain largely unchanged.
notable_changes: North-west industrial/commercial block gains extra buildings and parking areas.
Several vacant parcels converted to single-family housing, raising lot coverage slightly.
South-west school campus extended; synthetic turf and additional roofs appear.
Diagonal arterial/rail corridor shows widening and resurfacing over time.
Residential tree canopy thickens, indicating maturing vegetation and limited clearing.
